      "body" : "> It's very weird that QT uses string matching here on purpose\r\n\r\nYes. Qt's autodetection of html/plaintext for labels can be annoying, but this is a few magnitudes worse. The moral of the story is to leave as little a possible to defaults. Explicitly setting the role for all actions makes sense (if I remember correctly it also helps accessibility as screen readers and such use the info).",
